I'm a Junior Researcher in [Economics](https://www2.novasbe.unl.pt/en/faculty-research/research/research-unit/overview) at [Nova School of Business and Economics](https://www2.novasbe.unl.pt/en/), in Carcavelos (Portugal). 

email: joao.sousa@novasbe.pt


### Work in progress   

- "Taxes and Migration Flows: Preferential Tax Schemes for High-Skill Immigrants" [[CEPR working paper]](https://cepr.org/publications/dp18414), with [Pedro Teles](https://sites.google.com/view/pedroteles/)

- "Schooling and Lifetime Labor Supply" [[slides]](https://www.dropbox.com/s/csgat8n57yt4c5n/ageing_ISEG_June2022.pdf?dl=0)

- "Modeling Wealth and Income Inequality: Implications for Optimal Taxation", with [Pedro Brinca](https://pedrobrinca.pt), [Hans. A. Holter](https://sites.google.com/site/hansaholter/), and [Catarina Reis](https://clsbe.lisboa.ucp.pt/pt-pt/pessoa/catarina-reis)

- "Unemployment subsidies and layoff subsidies", with [Marta C. Lopes](https://sites.google.com/site/mcardosolopes/)

- ["Global Repository of Income Dynamics (GRID): Portugal Country team"](https://www.grid-database.org/), with [João B. Duarte](https://jbduarte.com/), [Pedro Brinca](https://pedrobrinca.pt), and [Pedro Portugal](https://www.bportugal.pt/economista/pedro-portugal).

### Publications

